@edition "2026.6"

-- D1(xxi) frontier guardrail. This program is VALID (it type-checks clean — a `_test`,
-- not a `_bad`), but it uses the PROPAGATE operator (`half(n)?` — unwrap an `Ok` payload,
-- or early-return the `Error` from the enclosing function). eval evaluates the subject and
-- either yields the `Ok` payload or throws a ReturnSignal carrying the `Error`; the compute
-- spine has no propagate lowering — `normComp`/`norm` reach the `Propagate` AST node and
-- refuse it (the `default` arm of `normComp`). The differential harness must report it
-- `unsupported` — a CLEAN refusal at the compiler frontier, never a miscompile.
--
-- This is the backend-slice analogue of a `_bad` twin: a backend slice adds no checker
-- rejection rule, so the guarantee under test is "the compiler refuses what it cannot
-- yet lower, loudly", asserted by the harness rather than by an error count. D1(ii)
-- moved the frontier PAST scalar `match`; D1(iii) PAST tuples; D1(iv) PAST ADT
-- constructors; D1(v) PAST records; D1(vi) PAST lists; D1(vii) PAST closures-as-values;
-- D1(viii) PAST first-class `def` references; D1(ix) PAST first-class BUILTIN references;
-- D1(x) PAST short-circuit `&&`/`||`; D1(xi) PAST non-tail `if` as a value; D1(xii) PAST
-- non-tail `match` as a value; D1(xiii) PAST multi-clause `def`s; D1(xiv) PAST reassignment;
-- D1(xv) PAST atom literals; D1(xvi) PAST duration literals; D1(xvii) PAST `for`
-- comprehensions; D1(xviii) PAST integer ranges; D1(xix) PAST index assignment; D1(xx) PAST
-- the `loop` construct; D1(xxi) PAST TYPE TESTS (`e is Ctor(b)`; see compile_typetest_test).
-- The frontier now sits at the PROPAGATE operator (`e?`). This file uses one, so it still
-- refuses; when propagate lowers (a later D1 slice, an unwrap-or-early-return on Result), it
-- flips from `unsupported` to a print with no edit.

def half(n: Number): Result(Number, String)
  if n % 2 == 0
    Ok(n / 2)
  else
    Error("odd")

def quarter(n: Number): Result(Number, String)
  let h = half(n)?
  half(h)

def main(): Effect [io] ()
  println(quarter(8))
  println(quarter(6))
